{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":880,"text":"Welcome to Bayeku,"},{"time":3120,"text":"a riverine community in Ikorodu, Lagos --"},{"time":6520,"text":"a vivid representation of several\nriverine communities across Nigeria,"},{"time":12920,"text":"communities whose waterways\nhave been infested"},{"time":16920,"text":"by an invasive aquatic weed;"},{"time":19800,"text":"communities where economic livelihoods\nhave been hampered:"},{"time":25080,"text":"fishing, marine transportation"},{"time":28320,"text":"and trading;"},{"time":29600,"text":"communities where fish yields\nhave diminished;"},{"time":33800,"text":"communities where schoolchildren\nare unable to go to school"},{"time":38440,"text":"for days, sometimes weeks, on end."},{"time":42760,"text":"Who would have thought that this plant"},{"time":45640,"text":"with round leaves, inflated stems,\nand showy, lavender flowers"},{"time":52400,"text":"would cause such havoc\nin these communities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":56200,"text":"The plant is known as water hyacinth"},{"time":59000,"text":"and its botanical name,\nEichhornia crassipes."},{"time":62320,"text":"Interestingly, in Nigeria,\nthe plant is also known by other names,"},{"time":66880,"text":"names associated with historical events,"},{"time":69760,"text":"as well as myths."},{"time":71680,"text":"In some places,\nthe plant is called Babangida."},{"time":75800,"text":"When you hear Babangida, you remember\nthe military and military coups."},{"time":80960,"text":"And you think: fear, restraint."},{"time":84320,"text":"In parts of Nigeria in the Niger Delta,\nthe plant is also known as Abiola."},{"time":89720,"text":"When you hear Abiola,\nyou remember annulled elections"},{"time":94160,"text":"and you think: dashed hopes."},{"time":96800,"text":"In the southwestern part of Nigeria,"},{"time":99360,"text":"the plant is known as Gbe'borun."},{"time":101600,"text":"Gbe'borun is a Yoruba phrase"},{"time":103400,"text":"which translates to \"gossip,\"\nor \"talebearer.\""},{"time":107400,"text":"When you think of gossip, you think:\nrapid reproduction, destruction."},{"time":113240,"text":"And in the Igala-speaking part of Nigeria,"},{"time":115800,"text":"the plant is known as A Kp'iye Kp'oma,"},{"time":118680,"text":"And when you hear that,\nyou think of death."},{"time":121400,"text":"It literally translates\nto \"death to mother and child.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":126280,"text":"I personally had my encounter\nwith this plant in the year 2009."},{"time":131160,"text":"It was shortly after I had relocated\nfrom the US to Nigeria."},{"time":136920,"text":"I'd quit my job in corporate America"},{"time":139480,"text":"and decided to take\nthis big leap of faith,"},{"time":142680,"text":"a leap of faith that came\nout of a deep sense of conviction"},{"time":146200,"text":"that there was a lot of work\nto do in Nigeria"},{"time":148360,"text":"in the area of sustainable development."},{"time":150840,"text":"And so here I was in the year 2009,"},{"time":153840,"text":"actually, at the end of 2009,"},{"time":156000,"text":"in Lagos on the Third Mainland Bridge."}]},{"cues":[{"time":159040,"text":"And I looked to my left\nand saw this very arresting image."},{"time":163720,"text":"It was an image of fishing boats"},{"time":165520,"text":"that had been hemmed in\nby dense mats of water hyacinth."},{"time":171280,"text":"And I was really pained by what I saw"},{"time":173680,"text":"because I thought to myself,"},{"time":175200,"text":"\"These poor fisherfolk,"},{"time":177080,"text":"how are they going\nto go about their daily activities"},{"time":181960,"text":"with these restrictions.\""},{"time":184080,"text":"And then I thought,\n\"There's got to be a better way.\""},{"time":187160,"text":"A win-win solution whereby\nthe environment is taken care of"},{"time":192200,"text":"by the weeds being cleared out of the way"},{"time":194600,"text":"and then this being turned\ninto an economic benefit"},{"time":197760,"text":"for the communities\nwhose lives are impacted the most"},{"time":200600,"text":"by the infestation of the weed."},{"time":203160,"text":"That, I would say, was my spark moment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":206760,"text":"And so I did further research\nto find out more"},{"time":210240,"text":"about the beneficial uses of this weed."},{"time":213200,"text":"Out of the several,\none struck me the most."},{"time":216640,"text":"It was the use of the plant\nfor handicrafts."},{"time":219760,"text":"And I thought, \"What a great idea.\""},{"time":222120,"text":"Personally, I love handicrafts,"},{"time":224520,"text":"especially handicrafts\nthat are woven around a story."},{"time":229200,"text":"And so I thought, \"This could be\neasily deployed within the communities"},{"time":233840,"text":"without the requirement\nof technical skills.\""},{"time":237400,"text":"And I thought to myself,\n\"Three simple steps to a mega solution.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":243040,"text":"First step: Get out into the waterways\nand harvest the water hyacinth."},{"time":248160,"text":"That way, you create access."}]},{"cues":[{"time":250480,"text":"Secondly, you dry\nthe water hyacinth stems."}]},{"cues":[{"time":255080,"text":"And thirdly, you weave\nthe water hyacinth into products."}]},{"cues":[{"time":260519,"text":"The third step was a challenge."},{"time":262920,"text":"See, I'm a computer scientist\nby background"},{"time":265640,"text":"and not someone in the creative arts."},{"time":268320,"text":"And so I began my quest"},{"time":270040,"text":"to find out how I can learn how to weave."}]},{"cues":[{"time":273000,"text":"And this quest took me\nto a community in Ibadan, where I lived,"},{"time":277160,"text":"called Sabo."},{"time":278600,"text":"Sabo translates to \"strangers' quarters.\""},{"time":281480,"text":"And the community is\npredominantly made up of people"},{"time":284520,"text":"from the northern part of the country."},{"time":286520,"text":"So I literally took\nmy dried weeds in hand,"},{"time":289480,"text":"there were several more of them,"},{"time":291080,"text":"and went knocking from door to door\nto find out who could teach me"},{"time":294440,"text":"how to weave these\nwater hyacinth stems into ropes."},{"time":298880,"text":"And I was directed\nto the shed of Malam Yahaya."},{"time":302880,"text":"The problem, though,\nis that Malam Yahaya doesn't speak English"},{"time":305920,"text":"and neither did I speak Hausa."},{"time":308040,"text":"But some little kids came to the rescue"},{"time":310200,"text":"and helped translate."},{"time":312000,"text":"And that began my journey\nof learning how to weave"},{"time":315280,"text":"and transform these\ndried water hyacinth stems"},{"time":319880,"text":"into long ropes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":323400,"text":"With my long ropes in hand,"},{"time":325680,"text":"I was now equipped to make products."},{"time":328800,"text":"And that was the beginning\nof partnerships."},{"time":331240,"text":"Working with rattan basket makers\nto come up with products."},{"time":335240,"text":"So with this in hand, I felt confident"},{"time":338040,"text":"that I would be able\nto take this knowledge"},{"time":340064,"text":"back into the riverine communities"},{"time":342640,"text":"and help them to transform\ntheir adversity into prosperity."},{"time":347920,"text":"So taking these weeds\nand actually weaving them"},{"time":351120,"text":"into products that can be sold."},{"time":353720,"text":"So we have pens, we have tableware,"},{"time":357480,"text":"we have purses, we have tissue boxes."},{"time":361280,"text":"Thereby, helping the communities"},{"time":363840,"text":"to see water hyacinth\nin a different light."},{"time":367040,"text":"Seeing water hyacinth as being valuable,"},{"time":369720,"text":"being aesthetic,\nbeing durable, tough, resilient."},{"time":375880,"text":"Changing names, changing livelihoods."}]},{"cues":[{"time":379280,"text":"From Gbe'borun, gossip,"},{"time":382280,"text":"to Olusotan, storyteller."},{"time":385120,"text":"And from A Kp'iye Kp'oma,\nwhich is \"killer of mother and child,\""},{"time":389160,"text":"to Ya du j'ewn w'Iye kp'Oma,"},{"time":391520,"text":"\"provider of food for mother and child.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":394920,"text":"And I'd like to end\nwith a quote by Michael Margolis."},{"time":398800,"text":"He said, \"If you want to learn\nabout a culture, listen to the stories."},{"time":403840,"text":"And if you want to change a culture,\nchange the stories.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":407920,"text":"And so, from Makoko community,\nto Abobiri, to Ewoi,"},{"time":413040,"text":"to Kolo, to Owahwa, Esaba,"},{"time":416720,"text":"we have changed the story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":419320,"text":"Thank you for listening."}]},{"cues":[{"time":420880,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}